      • reset

        public static void reset()

        Resets the precompiled PLUS pattern because in the next compile run it could be redefined.

      • setMultiple

        public void setMultiple(java.lang.String optId)
                 throws ParseException

        Sets the multiple option. This option indicates if the channel tickstamps are reverted at the end of the block.

        Parameters:
        optId - option ID (only needed for the exception description)
        Throws:
        ParseException - if this option has already been set for this block.

      • setQuantity

        public void setQuantity(int quantity,
                        java.lang.String optId)
                 throws ParseException

        Sets the quantity option. This option indicates how often the block is executed.

        Parameters:
        quantity - the quantity value
        optId - option ID (only needed for the exception description)
        Throws:
        ParseException - if this option has already been set for this block.

      • setTuplet

        public void setTuplet(java.lang.String tuplet,
                      java.lang.String optId)
               throws ParseException

        Sets the tuplet modifier. This modifier shortens all notes of this block according to the tuplet value. This applies for notes and rests as well as for child blocks.

        Parameters:
        tuplet -
        optId - option ID (only needed for the exception description)
        Throws:
        ParseException - if this option has already been set for this block.

      • applyTuplets

        public void applyTuplets(java.lang.String parentTuplets)

        Applies tuplets to all child elements.

        Parameters:
        parentTuplets - The tuplet modifiers from all (grand)parents to be applied as well.

      • add

        public void add(java.lang.Object element)

        Adds a new content element to this block. The content to be added can be one of the following objects:

        • an array of strings belonging to one source code line
        • another (nested) block
        Parameters:
        element - the content to be added

      • play

        public void play()
          throws ParseException

        Executes the content of the block.

        Throws:
        ParseException - if one of the content lines cannot be parsed.
